description: A scheduled site first observed from aerial photography. The site is triple-ditched and forms a square enclosure with a probable South-East entrance, suggested to be a religious enclosure but this is not certain. This site's entry here is very tentative, and may be removed based on further research.
bibliography: Bagnall-Smith, Jean. “Interim Report on the Votive Material from Romano-Celtic Temple Sites in Oxfordshire,” 1995.
Martyn, Blick, Brindle, and et al. “Lee’s Rest, Charlbury (Oxfordshire).” The Rural Settlement of Roman Britain: an online resource, 2015. https://doi.org/10.5284/1030449.
